title: Semaphore UI jobs
agents: special
catalog: applications
license: MIT
distribution: check_mk
description:
 This check monitors task states from the Semaphore UI REST API. It reports
 current jobs in running, waiting and transitional states, the age of the
 oldest job per active state, recent success/error/stopped counts, unknown
 statuses, invalid timestamps, and potentially incomplete API task history.

 The API connection is configured under Setup > Agents > Other integrations >
 Semaphore UI jobs. Thresholds are configured with the service monitoring rule
 Semaphore UI jobs.
discovery:
 One service named "Semaphore Jobs" is discovered when the special agent returns
 a semaphore_jobs section.
check:
 Running jobs are informational. WARN/CRIT defaults focus on queue accumulation,
 jobs that remain in transitional states too long, old running jobs, recent
 failed jobs, and incomplete or unexpected API data.

notes:
 Project summaries are displayed on separate lines. Semaphore currently limits
 the project task-list endpoint to 1,000 records. When that limit is reached,
 the service details identify the affected project, its ID, and the returned
 task range so the reason for the data-quality warning is visible.
